{"meta":{"updateDate":1755117017722,"pPcc":"SAT#P","questionId":"dd3b1e1a","skill_cd":"P.C.","score_band_range_cd":4,"skill_desc":"Nonlinear functions","createDate":1755117017722,"program":"SAT","primary_class_cd_desc":"Advanced Math","ibn":"","external_id":"b026eab4-9126-4926-ba7f-aeb53aa41e01","primary_class_cd":"P","uId":"3b7fa932-5a2a-4edd-8a89-ee1d37771e97","difficulty":"M"},"source":"modern","detail":{"type":"spr","stem":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><math alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals x Superscript 5 Baseline plus 9 x plus 17\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mrow><mn>9</mn></mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mrow><mn>17</mn></mrow></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For the given function <math alttext=\"f\"><mi>f</mi>\n</math>, the graph of&nbsp;<math alttext=\"y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math> in the <em>xy</em>-plane passes through the point <math alttext=\"left parenthesis 0 comma b right parenthesis\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>, where <math alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi>\n</math> is a constant. What is the value of <math alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi>\n</math>?</p>","keys":["17"],"rationale":"<p>The correct answer is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"17\"><mn>17</mn></math>. It's given that the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> in the <em>xy</em>-plane passes through the point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis 0 comma b right parenthesis\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>)</mo></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi></math> is a constant. It follows that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis 0 right parenthesis\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math> equals <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi></math>. Substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0\"><mn>0</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math> in the given function yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis 0 right parenthesis equals 0 Superscript 5 Baseline plus 9 left parenthesis 0 right parenthesis plus 17\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>0</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>17</mn></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis 0 right parenthesis equals 17\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>17</mn></math>. Therefore, the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"17\"><mn>17</mn></math>.</p>","externalid":"b026eab4-9126-4926-ba7f-aeb53aa41e01","correct_answer":["17"]}}